## Merge Checklist

• Add specs that demonstrate bug / test a new feature.
• Update <https://docs.ohc.network|product documentation>.
• Ensure that UI text is kept in I18n files.
• Prep screenshot or demo video for changelog entry, and attach it to issue.
• Request for Peer Reviews
• Completion of QA in Mobile Devices
• Completion of QA in Desktop Devices

## Summary by CodeRabbit

## Summary by CodeRabbit

• *New Features*  
   • Enhanced patient discharge workflow by adding a dedicated section to enter and view discharge summary advice.  
   • Introduced new controls for marking patients for discharge, including options to set discharge date and time.  
   • Improved user interface messaging and labels for clearer, more guided discharge-related actions.  
   • Added support for additional discharge-related information in the system's data structures, including new properties for handling discharge advice.  
   • New section for displaying discharge information, including date, time, and summary advice.  
   • Conditional rendering of discharge summary advice based on encounter status, with toggle functionality for text visibility.  
   • Added alert dialog for confirming discharge actions, improving user awareness before finalizing discharges.  
   • Streamlined the process of updating discharge details and managing patient status.  
   • New labels and messages to enhance clarity around discharge confirmation and summary advice.

• Requires the following backend: <https://github.com/ohcnetwork/care_teleicu_devices/pull/8|ohcnetwork/care_teleicu_devices#8>
• Fixes <https://github.com/ohcnetwork/care_teleicu_devices_fe/issues/19|#19>

Enhance camera position presets management by adding sorting functionality and batch update support

• Introduced `useReorderMutation` hook for handling the reordering of camera presets.
• Updated `PresetDropdown` and `CameraPositionPresets` components to support sorting by `sort_index`.
• Added batch request capability to `cameraPositionPresetApi` for efficient updates.
• Improved UI with new icons for reordering presets and adjusted accessibility attributes.

This update aligns with the microfrontend architecture by ensuring efficient state management and enhancing user experience in the camera configuration workflow.
